      "id": "1e5f9535_c6ce410d",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/api/impl/events/cmsubscription/service/CmNotificationSubscriptionPersistenceServiceImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 123,
      "message": "There's a few issues here around quotes, e.g. id value is both single and double-quoted (note Json does not support single-quotes). I think Java 17 multi-line strings make quotes much easier to handle, something like this:\n\n    updatedJson = \"\"\"\n        {\"cm-handle\":[{\"id\":\"%s\",\"filters\":{\"filter\":[\n          {\"xpath\": \"%s\",\"subscriptionIds\": [\"%s\"]}]}}]}\n        \"\"\".formatted(cmHandleId, xpath, newSubscriptionId);",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
      },
      "updated": "2024-03-21 16:31:58.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "6a32bd1e_bda5316c",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/api/impl/events/cmsubscription/service/CmNotificationSubscriptionPersistenceServiceImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 123,
      "message": "Alternatively, if you prefer structures, can do something like - I prefer this to raw strings because it automatically takes care of escaping special characters like \":\n\n    updatedJson = jsonObjectMapper.asJsonString(\n        Map.of(\"cm-handle\", Map.of(\"id\", cmHandleId, \n            \"filters\", Map.of(\"filter\", Map.of(\"xpath\", xpath, \n                \"subscriptionIds\", List.of(newSubscriptionId))))));",
      "author": {
